snippet.textDisplay: I am not much of a basketball fan and have always been nothing but a bookworm. The celebrity athletes that I know can be easily counted in one hand and still have too many fingers. I may have heard of Kobe’s name before, but until this accident, I never really knew who he was. Despite that, I watched this farewell and the many farewells of his friends, colleagues, and family. Watching this made me realize just how great and kind of a person he was. I was touched and it is such a pity to lose someone respectable and kind like him and his daughter. It is such a pity that Gianna couldn’t grow up and that such a happy family was broken like this. Truly, I give my sympathy. May they Rest In Peace.

snippet.textDisplay:
As a Dad who's lost his eldest son, I am truly in awe of how she stepped up there and exuded so much strength and grace, under the most difficult of circumstances. She lost her baby and her soul mate on that dreadful day and we should've all been moved to tears after hearing her heartfelt words about her beloved child and husband. Undeniably, a special woman and it's no wonder Kobe fell in love with her and it's no wonder she gave birth to such a beautiful and strong force of nature, young queen Gianna. Kobe and GiGi are surely smiling from paradise, both so proud of her.

My prayers will continue to go out to the entire Bryant family and the Laker nation as a whole.
